# CTG install status (Hacker Planet LLC)

## Canonical paths

| Role | Path |
|------|------|
| **Repo (develop here)** | `$env:USERPROFILE\Programs\Hacker Planet LLC\cyberThreatGotchi` |
| **Legacy stub** | `$env:USERPROFILE\Projects\cyberThreatGotchi` — sync only; reopen Cursor on Programs |
| **Ecosystem clones** | `$env:USERPROFILE\Programs\Hacker Planet LLC\<repo-name>` |

Path helpers: `scripts/windows/CTG-Paths.ps1` (`Get-CtgRepoRoot`, `Get-CtgProgramsRoot`).

## Source of truth

Run **`.\scripts\windows\Invoke-CtgInstallAudit.ps1`** before claiming something is installed.

- Text log: `%USERPROFILE%\Backups\logs\ctg-install-audit-*.txt`
- JSON (optional): `-Json` → `ctg-install-audit-latest.json`
- Status values: **INSTALLED** | **PENDING** | **MANUAL** | **OPTIONAL**

Re-run after Admin task registration, vault init, Docker/Wazuh, or Kali staging.

## Never break (pass statuses)

- **DuckDuckGo VPN / DNS / Password Manager** — do not install competing VPNs or change DNS without `Preserve-DuckDuckGoVpn.ps1` review.
- **HVCI / VBS / kernel mitigations / spec-ctrl** — never disable for “performance”; Kali `<SpecCtrl enabled="true"/>` is intentional (RETBleed lab).
- **Kali display / seamless** — do not reset VRAM, Wayland, or Guest Additions settings without Andy’s ask; use CLICK-ME / share trigger, not guest-flash retry loops.
- **Wi-Fi repair** — `Repair-WindowsWifi.ps1 -ApplyFixes` only when Wi-Fi is up and DDG preserve is verified.

